body:
Why does IE 7 not handle, the css background property for anchors?

css:

	.nav a
	{
	    float: left;
	    display: block;
	    padding: 5px;
	    height: 25px;
	    line-height: 25px;
	    font-weight: bold;
	}
	.nav a:hover
	{
	    background: #fff;
	    color: #000;
	}


html:

	<div class="nav">
	    <a href="#">anchor</a>
	</div>


It has no background, but only in ie7. Why?
